
[1]ghastly

   GH`ASTLY, a. [Eng. gush, gust.]

   1. Like a ghost in appearance; deathlike; pale; dismal; as a ghastly
   face; ghastly smiles.

   2. Horrible; shocking; dreadful.

   Mangled with ghastly wounds.
